; BuildPlacementHandler is placed AFTER ClickHandler / BoxSelectHandler /
; DoubleClickSelect in sibling order so its _unhandled_input runs FIRST.
; Godot dispatches _unhandled_input in REVERSE sibling order — the
; higher-index sibling fires first. Verified by the regression test
; `test_godot_unhandled_input_dispatch_order` in
; tests/unit/test_godot_unhandled_input_dispatch_order.gd.
;
; BUG-10 fix (2026-05-14): the wave-1C placement put BPH at idx 4
; (between AttackMoveHandler and ClickHandler) under the mistaken
; "lower-index = first" convention copied from AttackMoveHandler. That
; convention is backwards; ClickHandler at the lower index actually
; fired first and consumed every terrain click via deselect-all,
; preventing BPH from ever reaching its confirm-click handler. The
; selection-changed guard in BPH then cancelled the orphaned placement
; state. Live-test #2 surfaced this; the log diagnostic at
; `[click] LEFT: hit non-unit → deselect_all` arriving BEFORE the
; `[build-placement] BUG-08 guard` line was the smoking gun.
;
; When in placement mode the handler calls
; get_viewport().set_input_as_handled() so ClickHandler / BoxSelect /
; DoubleClickSelect never see the confirm-click. When not in placement
; mode the handler short-circuits and lets the other handlers run
; normally.
[node name="BuildPlacementHandler" type="Node" parent="."]
script = ExtResource("13_buildplacement")

[node name="HealthBarsOverlay" parent="." instance=ExtResource("9_healthbars")]

